  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The [contributing guide](https://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/blob/master/src/contributing.md) should be extended with reasoning why Layouts are superior to anchors and hardcoded sizes. It should also suggest when to use Layouts and when to use Positioners.  [Code examples](https://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/blob/master/src/code-examples.md) should also be provided.\r\n\r\n#### Motivation\r\nA lot of current QML components were developed in a non-reusable/non-flexible way, symptoms are: \r\n- hardcoded magic numbers for `x` and `y` positions, which makes components feasible only for one scenario (this applies more to status-desktop)\r\n- anchors used for positioning items in a row or column, which makes components unnecessarily complex and error-prone, increasing maintenance burden, [see example](https://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/pull/695/files#diff-757e842f8dd9e5ef1b55d732676873c31b19005d3b09b4164c753e5dd61c4e8f)\r\n\r\nIf we continue the way we do now, every component will need to be rewritten to adapt to new responsive designs.",
