    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Idea: how about adding size specifications to controls (at least StatusQ) and mentioning them in the component's documentation. Example:\r\n\r\n- Scrollable [W/H] - will effectively use more space available until all the content is displayed; e.g. scrollable content area\r\n- Resizable [W/H] - can be resizable until maxWidth/maxHeight but the extra space won't bring much value either; e.g. labels/values\r\n- Scalable [W/H] - can be resized but the content proportions stay the same (not recommended more than maxWidth/maxHeight) e.g. clock widget\r\n- Fixed - extra space will break the control; e.g. panels with specific space/relation between fixed controls",
